{"word":"χρυσοκόμης","slug":"χρυσοκόμης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χρυσοκόμης</b></el> <el>(χρῡσο-κόμης, ου,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κόμη'><el>κόμη</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>the golden haired</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>;— <el>ὁ Χρ.</el> <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> for Apollo, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>with golden ornaments in the hair</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}